{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Cslib/Foundations/Data/Relation.html#Relation.reduction_sys\"><span class=\"name\">Relation</span>.<span class=\"name\">reduction_sys</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"This attribute calls the `reduction_notation` command for the annotated declaration, such as in:\n\n```\n@[reduction_sys \"ₙ\", simp]\ndef PredReduction (a b : ℕ) : Prop := a = b + 1\n```\n","docLink":"./Cslib/Foundations/Data/Relation.html#Relation.reduction_sys","kind":"def","line":461,"name":"Relation.reduction_sys","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/cslib/blob/b00648a4fe741981bb586a3cc845258ab1583f61/Cslib/Foundations/Data/Relation.lean#L461-L469"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Cslib/Foundations/Data/Relation.html#Relation.command_Reduction_notation__\"><span class=\"name\">Relation</span>.<span class=\"name\">command_Reduction_notation__</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"This command adds notations for relations. This should not usually be called directly, but from\nthe `reduction_sys` attribute.\n\nAs an example `reduction_notation foo \"β\"` will add the notations \"⭢β\" and \"↠β\".\n\nNote that the string used will afterwards be registered as a notation. This means that if you have\nalso used this as a constructor name, you will need quotes to access corresponding cases, e.g. «β»\nin the above example.\n","docLink":"./Cslib/Foundations/Data/Relation.html#Relation.command_Reduction_notation__","kind":"def","line":433,"name":"Relation.command_Reduction_notation__","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/cslib/blob/b00648a4fe741981bb586a3cc845258ab1583f61/Cslib/Foundations/Data/Relation.lean#L433-L443"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Cslib/Foundations/Data/Relation.html#Relation.RightUnique.toConfluent\"><span class=\"name\">Relation</span>.<span class=\"name\">RightUnique</span>.<span class=\"name\">toConfluent</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">r</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hr</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Relator.html#Relator.RightUnique\">Relator.RightUnique</a> <span class=\"fn\">r</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Cslib/Foundations/Data/Relation.html#Relation.Confluent\">Confluent</a> <span class=\"fn\">r</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`Relator.RightUnique` corresponds to deterministic reductions, which are confluent, as all\nmulti-reductions with a common origin start the same (this fact is\n`Relation.ReflTransGen.total_of_right_unique`.) ","docLink":"./Cslib/Foundations/Data/Relation.html#Relation.RightUnique.toConfluent","kind":"theorem","line":420,"name":"Relation.RightUnique.toConfluent","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/cslib/blob/b00648a4fe741981bb586a3cc845258ab1583f61/Cslib/Foundations/Data/Relation.lean#L420-L427"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"de